    <p>
      The width abstraction is extremely handy for a number of reasons:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        It is not the job of any given component of our codebase to govern it's own width.
      </li>
      <li>
        Given the previously rule, in responsive environments, media-queries can be hooked onto widths themselves, and not the objects.
      </li>
      <li>
        Abstracting a commonly used set of rules helps to keep the code base small and maintainable.
      </li>
    </ul>
